added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: Kabooms Part 1
added.description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

added.title: Kabooms Part 2
added.description: Inspired by the "Babies vs Dogs" movie, the Titans decide to make a big Hollywood film of their own.

added.title: Tower Renovation
added.description: Following the destruction of their Tower by Slade, the Titans go house hunting.

added.title: My Name Is Jose
added.description: The Titans have Raven give them new super powers but have a hard time adjusting.

added.title: The Power of Shrimps
added.description: Aqualad uses shrimps and prime rib to win back Raven.

added.title: Monster Squad!
added.description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: Quantum Fun
added.description: Robin takes the other Titans on a trip through the dizzying world of quantum physics.

added.title: The Fight
added.description: Robin tries to teach the other Titans about real estate, but they're only interested in finding a villain to fight.

added.title: The Groover
added.description: Robin takes the Titans on an educational trip to the Grand Canyon.

added.title: How's This for a Special? Spaaaace Part 1
added.description: After receiving a galactic crime alert, the Titans take off for an epic space adventure.

added.title: BBRBDAY
added.description: When he isn't invited to Beast Boy's birthday party, Robin throws his own party, with special guest Bob Uecker.

added.title: How's This for a Special? Spaaaace Part 2
added.description: The Titans have to stop Darkseid's latest scheme, but the excitement of the space adventure might be too much for Robin to handle.

added.title: Slapping Butts and Celebrating for No Reason
added.description: When the Big Game is threatened the Titans must infiltrate the football stadium and stop the attack.

added.title: Nostalgia Is Not a Substitute for an Actual Story
added.description: The Titans time travel back to the 1980s to determine whether or not it was the best decade ever.

added.title: Business Ethics Wink Wink
added.description: Starfire dreams of becoming a successful business alien princess and joins a cookie-selling organization to learn the proper skills.

added.title: Genie President
added.description: Robin hatches a plan to get rich off pennies, but Starfire believes they are magical.

added.title: Tall Titan Tales
added.description: Robin tries to tell some tall tales but the other Titans give their own fractured versions instead.

added.title: I Used to Be a Peoples
added.description: Robin feels the other Titans are spending too much time together so he encourages them to spend some time alone.

added.title: The Metric System vs. Freedom
added.description: Robin teaches the other Titans about the difference between the Imperial System and the Metric System.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds another talent competition to find the second best superhero team in the world.

added.title: The Chaff
added.description: In an effort to get Teen Titan Go! canceled, Control Freak shows off some deleted scenes.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition Part 2
added.description: The competition heats up and the Titans must find a way to beat the Hive Five.

added.title: Them Soviet Boys
added.description: In order to quickly get through their chores and karate lessons, the Titans learn how to montage

added.title: Little Elvis
added.description: The Titans team up with Shazam in order to defeat the evil Mr. Mind.

added.title: Booty Eggs
added.description: Not wanting to be creeped out on Easter the Titans dispatch the Easter Bunny and take matters into their own hands.

added.title: TV Knight 4
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon go camping but instead of fun outdoor activities they'd rather watch TV.

added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: Don't Be An Icarus
added.description: Robin tries to tell some Greek myths but the other Titans give their own fractured versions instead.

added.title: Stockton, CA!
added.description: The Titans must find a way to keep all the Jump City residents from moving to Stockton.

added.title: What's Opera, Titans?
added.description: Robin surprises the Titans with a trip to the opera but they soon fall asleep, and all dream about starring in their own operas.

added.title: Forest Pirates
added.description: The Titans are at Super Hero Summer Camp for the week and they may need to add another teammate to win the big canoe race.

added.title: The Bergerac
added.description: The Titans give Robin advice to guide him through his camp romance with Wonder Girl.

added.title: Snot and Tears
added.description: Robin tells the Titans to stop being reckless teens or the Creepy Catcher will get them.

added.title: What We Learned at Camp
added.description: After not receiving participation medals, the Titans must demonstrate what they learned at camp.

added.title: Campfire!
added.description: The Titans put on a show but Robin warns that the performance must be boring or else they'll wake up the wolves.

added.title: Communicate Openly
added.description: Bumbleebee becomes the 6th Titan and moves into the Tower but has a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Royal Jelly
added.description: Bumblebee offers to help Robin with his leadership skills by teaching him how to act like a queen bee.

added.title: Strength of a Grown Man
added.description: Needing a hero with shrinking powers, but forgetting about Bumblebee, Robin invites The Atom to join their fight against the Brain.

added.title: Had to Be There
added.description: So she isn't left out of inside jokes, the Titans time travel to past adventures and insert Bumblebee into their memories.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 1
added.description: The Girls Night Out Crew decide to stay in and have a slumber party but an unknown alien threat descends on Jump City.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 2
added.description: When Blackfire begins her plan to conquer Earth, the girls must pull out all the stops to defeat her.

added.title: The Great Disaster
added.description: Robin gets amnesia and starts thinking that Hawkman is his mother.

added.title: The Viewers Decide
added.description: It's Titans West vs Titans East as the two teams compete for who gets Bumblebee.

added.title: Cartoon Feud
added.description: Control Freak forces the Titans and the Scooby Gang to compete on Family Feud.

added.title: Curse of the Booty Scooty
added.description: When Robin Booty Scootys his butt off, the Titans must go on an adventure to recover the lost booty.

added.title: Collect Them All
added.description: After the other Titans are turned into collectibles and disappear, Robin must search yard sales and stores to find them.

added.title: TV Knight 5
added.description: Batman pretends to be sick to avoid work so he and Commissioner Gordon can run around town watching their favorite shows.

added.title: Butt Atoms
added.description: Despite Robin's warning, the Titans mess around with atomic toots and end up causing a worldwide plague.

added.title: Witches Brew
added.description: The Titans throw a Halloween party and invite the Justice League but the witches brew Robin creates has side effects.

added.title: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 1
added.description: In this episode of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans gain the ability to transform into cars.

added.title: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 2
added.description: In the exciting conclusion of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans must learn to work together to stop Dr. Military.

added.title: Chapter 1: NBTS Special
added.description: Cyborg becomes trapped in the alternate reality of Night Begins to Shine with a Dragon who wants to steal the song for his own evil purposes.

added.title: Chapter 2: NBTS Special
added.description: Without Cyborg, Beast Boy feels lost and sets out to find himself, but ends up meeting a music legend.

added.title: Chapter 3: NBTS Special
added.description: The Titans return to the alternate reality to save Cyborg but will they be able to defeat the Dragon?

added.title: Chapter 4: NBTS Special
added.description: In a final epic battle, the Titans and their musician friends square off against the Dragon for control of The Night Begins to Shine.

added.title: Hey You, Don't Forget About Me in Your Memory
added.description: Robin convinces the Titans to go back to school with him so he can finally become the all-American class president-type he's dreamed of being.

added.title: Teen Titans Go! vs. Teen Titans
added.description: Earths collide when the mysterious "Master of Games" appears over Titans Tower and throws the Teen Titans in a fight against their taller, more serious selves. Now, our heroes must set aside their differences and work together to stop him. It's a crisis of multiverse proportions that will take nothing less than two versions of the Teen Titans to solve!

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Bug City
added.description: Craig discovers a bunch of bugs under a rock and decides to build them a city.

added.title: The Kids
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's voices may be breaking, but they're showing no signs of growing up. Whilst Gumball and Darwin make fun of Mom and Dad for being old, their voices start to break. They try to ignore it, but everybody they meet reacts to their new and unpredictable voices. Gumball and Darwin finally decide to make the most of their childhood whilst there's still time.

added.title: The Mirror
added.description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

added.title: The Man
added.description: It's Granny Jojo's Birthday and she's brought an unexpected guest to dinner. Granny Jojo has brought a boyfriend to her birthday meal and Dad isn't happy about it. He bans Granny JoJo from ever seeing Louis again. When the kids get caught sneaking Granny Jojo out of the house, Dad challenges Louis to a man-off to prove once and for all who is the man of the house?!!

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: The Pony
added.description: Gumball and Darwin race home to spend quality time with Anais, but every likely obstacle gets in way... and some unlikely ones too!

added.title: Positive Attitude Theory
added.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

added.title: Follow Your Dreams
added.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: The Limo
added.description: To help distract Panda from his girl problems, Grizz and Ice Bear treat him to a ride in a limo.

added.title: More Everyone's Tube
added.description: Through another video browsing session online, we get more videos uploaded by the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

added.title: Bunnies
added.description: The Baby Bears meet a group of helpless bunnies. When they find out the bunnies live in fear of vicious crows, the Bears decide to become heroes and help out.

added.title: Panda 2
added.description: Baby Panda happily lives in a closed off environment for study. But when he's given a new friend, Panda 2, his worldview is shaken, which sets him off on a great adventure.

added.title: Lazer Royale
added.description: The Baby Bears sign up for a game of laser tag, hoping to win some ice cream. But, the round of laser tag turns out to be less of a game and more like a war zone.

added.title: Baby Bears Can't Jump
added.description: In order to win a pizza, the Baby Bears play basketball against a ragtag gang of kids.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: The Big Show
added.description: Steven shoots a documentary that follows a local band as they get their first big break.

added.title: Pool Hopping
added.description: Garnet and Steven explore the most unlikely timelines in Beach City.

added.title: Letters to Lars
added.description: Steven writes about the latest news of Beach City.

added.title: Can't Go Back
added.description: Ronaldo spots something mysterious on the moon, and Steven goes to investigate.

added.title: A Single Pale Rose
added.description: Steven helps Pearl find her phone.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: Duck Duck Juice
added.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

added.title: Stop! Hamster Time
added.description: Owen takes over the job of caring for the class hamster and learns that he's evil.

added.title: Driving Miss Crazy
added.description: Duncan leads Beth to believe she's broken his battery-powered bike and makes her chauffeur him around in a wagon for the day as punishment.

added.title: Weiner Takes All
added.description: After forgetting to book a Hot Diggity Doggity Dog mascot on National Hotdog Day, Chef tries to pass off an Australian man dressed as a kangaroo as a substitute.

added.title: Apoca-lice Now
added.description: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

added.title: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
added.description: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

added.title: Look Who's Clocking
added.description: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

added.title: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
added.description: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

added.title: Bomzobo Lives
added.description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

added.title: Animorphosis
added.description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: High Stress Express
added.description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 1
added.description: With new Omni-Enhancements in tow, Ben looks to save a town from a sudden mudslide, but his heroics are short lived once Vilgax appears to warn our hero about the consequences of the Omnitrix's mysterious new alien.

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 2
added.description: After discovering that Vilgax has joined forces with the Weatherheads to trick him into turning over the Omnitrix, Ben must not only overcome his doubts, but fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat his foes.

added.title: Half-Sies
added.description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Xingo's Back
added.description: Left to entertain himself as Max takes a much deserved nap, Ben stumbles upon a Xingo arcade game and goes OE-Shock Rock to power it up, but when it receives too much juice, Xingo leaps out into the real world and our hero must go toe-to-toe with his favorite cartoon character.

added.title: Bounty Ball
added.description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

added.title: Strange Bedfellows
added.description: After an insane battle, MM and OS end up in the same hospital room. But even in full body casts, the sworn enemies continue the fight.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Zing Your Heart Out
added.description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
added.description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Adoradad
added.description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.
added.originalseriesname: Mao Mao, Heroes of Pure Heart

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Captured Clops
added.description: Badgerclops is tired of his responsibilities at Sheriff's HQ, so he joins the Sky Pirates.

added.title: Hall of Egress
added.description: Trapped and alone, Finn must unravel the riddle of the weird cave with no exit.

added.title: Jake the Brick
added.description: Jake sets out to fulfill a bizarre lifelong ambition.

added.title: Hoots
added.description: A charismatic stranger in Finn's dream leads Cosmic Owl to shirk his duties.

added.title: Hot Diggity Doom
added.description: It's election day in the Candy Kingdom but Princess Bubblegum's attention is diverted by a mysterious presence in the sky.

added.title: Jakesuit
added.description: Jake is sick and tired of Finn using his body as a suit of armor so he convinces Finn to trade places to show him how much it really stinks.

added.title: James
added.description: Finn and Jake are excited when Princess Bubblegum invites them to help her collect samples in the Desert of Wonders. But when their vessel is attacked by nasty goo monsters, Finn and Jake start to think the mission has been sabotaged by Princess Bubblegum's robot helper James.

added.title: Billy's Bucket List
added.description: Finn finds the hero Billy's bucket list and decides to complete the unfinished items as a final tribute.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: Hug Wolf
added.description: After an encounter with a Hug Wolf, Finn goes through a Jekyll and Hyde-like transformation becoming a hug-wolf himself!

added.title: Ignition Point
added.description: When Finn and Jake sneak into the Fire Kingdom, they get caught in the middle of a Flame family feud.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: Level Thirteen
added.description: Cyrus Borg discovers a shocking secret about Prime Empire, while the ninja battle an escaped Mechanic in their attempt to reach Level Thirteen and enter the game themselves.

added.title: Superstar Rockin' Jay
added.description: Now inside the Prime Empire game, the ninja find themselves in unfamiliar territory, ignorant of the rules of this world, as they try to find Zane and escape Unagami's army of Red Visors.

added.title: I Am Okino
added.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

added.title: The Glitch
added.description: In order to stop Unagami the ninja must obtain three Key-tanas, the first of which is hidden in the game zone Terra Kerana, one of Prime Empire's most dangerous game environments.

added.title: Wasted True Potential
added.description: In the wake of the previous season's victory, the ninja have gone soft and Master Wu must remind them of who they truly are.

added.title: Questing For Quests
added.description: Realizing they have gone soft, the ninja search for a quest to reignite their Spinjitzu training. Unfortunately, NINJAGO City is enjoying a period of rare tranquility.

added.title: Once and for All
added.description: Nya, Jay, Cole and Kai face off against the Ice Emperor's dreaded dragon, while Lloyd and his newfound allies, Kataru and Grimfax, confront the Ice Emperor himself.

added.title: Awakenings
added.description: The dramatic conclusion of the Never-Realm saga, in which old friends are reunited and the power of friendship is pitted against the corrupting power of the Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu.

added.title: Upgrade
added.description: The Mechanic has been receiving mechanical assistance from a mysterious helper, but it's not just the machines that need improving. The mechanic would like to improve himself as well, namely his own two mechanical arms, which are incapable of feeling.

added.title: Manhunt
added.description: Jay makes a desperate journey across an unfamiliar city, helped by a mysterious new ally, Scott.

added.title: Gayle Gossip: A Closer Look
added.description: Gayle Gossip investigates the Prime Empire phenomenon in a special news report.

added.title: The Stowaway
added.description: Lost and hunted in a strange city, Jay hides in the trunk of a car, only to wind up in a death defying chase, pursued by menacing Red Visors. But, unexpected help comes from the driver of the car he chose to stowaway inside of, and Jay makes an unlikely new ally.

added.title: Ninjago The Meaning of Victory
added.description: Interviews with the Speedway Five Billion Racecar Drivers reveal what they believe is at stake in the quest for the Keytana.

added.title: Let's Dance
added.description: Nya convinces Jay to take dance lessons with her, but finds, to her surprise, that Jay is a natural dancer whereas she is not. But by working together, the pair discover their rhythm again and find that they aren't as out of sync as they first thought.

added.title: Chip's Damage
added.description: Elodie enlists KO to help figure out what to do about Chip Damage.

added.title: You're a Good Friend, KO
added.description: KO brings Dendy along for a hero mission in order to cheer her up.

added.title: Crossover Nexus
added.description: When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes and they band together to escape.

added.title: Final Exams
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up with an unlikely ally to take on an unlikely foe.

added.title: You Have To Care
added.description: When an old friend of Enid's comes to town, she gets the opportunity to right an ancient wrong.

added.title: Stuck in an Elevator
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to go to a reunion concert.

added.title: El silencioso
added.description: Mientras que Lloyd y Harumi se aventuran a lo profundo de "Primeval's Eye" en busca de la tercer máscara Oni, los ninja tratan de arreglar al Bounty y hacer un descubrimiento sorprendente.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Quiet One
added.description: As Lloyd and Harumi venture deep into Primeval's Eye in search of the third Oni Mask, the ninja attempt to fix the Bounty and make a startling discovery.

added.title: Juego de mascaras
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y Harumi buscan el templo Oni para la última máscara, los ninjas son tomados como rehenes y descubren que verdaderas intensiones de la Princesa Harumi.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Game of Masks
added.description: As Lloyd and Harumi search the Oni Temple for the last mask, the ninja are taken hostage and discover Princess Harumi's true intentions.

added.title: Terror llegando
added.description: Los ninjas recurren al comisionado de la policía de Ninjago en un esfuerzo por ayudar a salvar a Lloyd y frustrar los esfuerzos de Harumi de resucitar al malvado Lord Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dread on Arrival
added.description: The ninja appeal to the police commissioner of Ninjago in an effort to help save Lloyd and thwart Harumi's efforts to resurrect the evil Lord Garmadon.

added.title: Struck by Lightning
added.description: Muscle Man and High Five Ghost get struck by lightning and can't remember each other.

added.title: El verdadero potencial
added.description: Justo cuando los ninjas piensan que han salvado el día, Lord Garmadon regresa a Ninjago, y libera a Harumi, quien lo anima a "alcanzar su verdadero potencial" conquistando lo único que siempre se interpuso en su camino, su hijo, Lloyd.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: True Potential
added.description: Just when the Ninja think they have saved the day, Lord Garmadon returns to Ninjago, and frees Harumi, who encourages him to "achieve his true potential" by conquering the one thing that has always stood in his way, his son, Lloyd.

added.title: Ninjago chico, problemas grandes
added.description: Los ninjas corres a salvar a Lloyd. Un Lord Garmadon más poderoso que nunca, crea una enorme estatua para ayudarlo a gobernar Ninjago y a derrotar a los ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Big Trouble, Little NinjaGo
added.description: The ninja race to save Lloyd, as a more powerful-than-ever Lord Garmadon creates an enormous Colossi to help him rule Ninjago and defeat the ninja.

added.title: Survival Skills
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to bring Benson some tortillas.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Uncle Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in trouble! If only he could call an Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: El gran espectaculo
added.description: Steven filma un documental que sigue los pasos de una banda local mientras consiguen su primer gran oportunidad.

added.title: De laguna en laguna
added.description: Garnet y Steven exploran las líneas de tiempo más improbables de Ciudad Playa.

added.title: Cartas para Lars
added.description: Steven escribe sobre las últimas novedades de Ciudad Playa.

added.title: No puedo regresar
added.description: Ronaldo divisa algo misterioso en la luna, y Steven sale a investigar.

added.title: What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

added.title: Una sola rosa palida
added.description: Steven ayuda a Perla a encontrar su teléfono.

added.title: Salsa Picante
added.description: La búsqueda de su salsa picante favorita hace que los Osos se involucren en una operación de picadura.

added.title: Mama a la Orden
added.description: Con el deseo de tener la experiencia de una madre, los osos usan una aplicación que les traerá una madre a la puerta de sus casas.

added.title: La Limosna
added.description: Para ayudar a Panda a distraerse de sus problemas románticos, Pardo y Polar le regalan un paseo en limosina.

added.title: Mas del canal de todos
added.description: A través de otra sesión de navegación por Internet, vemos más videos subidos por los Osos y sus amigos.

added.title: El Benefactor
added.description: Los Osos ayudan a Chloe a presentar su proyecto de ciencias para un concurso escolar. Pero el rival de Chloe complica las cosas.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: A Gift for Gus
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's present for Mr. Gus gets loose and causes trouble.

added.title: Bucky and the Howl
added.description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

added.title: Stick Hockey
added.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Tree of Life
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Super Alien Hero Buddy Adventures
added.description: Ben discovers his alien heroes have been ripped off by a lame cartoon and he is not happy. So he sets out to make things right.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Sugar Rush
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

added.title: El Onceavo Alienigena Parte 1
added.description: Con sus nuevas Omni-Mejoras, Ben intenta salvar una ciudad de un repentino alud. Pero su heroísmo dura poco, porque llega Vilgax a advertirlo de las consecuencias del misterioso alien del Omnitrix.

added.title: El Onceavo Alienigena Parte 2
added.description: Ben descubre que Vilgax se ha unido a los Weatherheads para obligarlo a entregar el Omnitrix. Ahora no solo deberá superar sus dudas, sino también aceptar sus nuevos poderes, si es que quiere derrotar a sus enemigos.

added.title: A Media
added.description: Durante un viaje al Lago de los Ozarks, Ben y Gwen discuten sobre la innecesaria celebración de "medio cumpleaños" de Ben. Pero cuando Max se entera de un sospechoso desprendimiento de rocas cercano, los primos deben dejar de lado sus diferencias si quieren rescatar a los mineros atrapados y revelar quién está detrás de la catástrofe producida por el hombre antes de que sea demasiado tarde: los hermanos Bugg.

added.title: Parley Part 1
added.description: Megatron and Optimus parley in an attempt to unite against Starscream.

added.title: El regreso de Xingo
added.description: Cuando Ben debe divertirse solo durante la merecida siesta de Max, se topa con un juego de Xingo y decide convertirse en OE-Shock Rock para encenderlo. Pero cuando Xingo recibe demasiada carga, salta al mundo real, y nuestro héroe debe quedar frente a frente con su personaje animado favorito.

added.title: Parley Part 2
added.description: The Autobot-Decepticon peace talks breaks down after Slipstream returns with a dire warning.

added.title: Starscream's Children Part 1
added.description: The Autobots received a distress call from the Nemesis and must come to the aid of their arch-enemies.

added.title: Cazarecompensas
added.description: Mientras Gwen escucha una conferencia sobre el Ferrocarril Transcontinental, Ben se escapa en secreto a la tienda de regalos. Pero una vez que los Cazarrecompensas aparecen y acorralan a nuestro héroe, Gwen debe transmitir la información que aprendió en el tren y utilizarla para ayudar a Ben a escapar.

added.title: Starscream's Children Part 2
added.description: Starscream reveals his scraplet army, incapacitating the Autobots and Decepticons and setting up a show down between him and Cheetor.

added.title: Spotted Part 1
added.description: Worried about finding a useful position among the Autobots, Cheetor learns how to become an Autobot Scout from Bumblebee.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Spotted Part 2
added.description: Cheetor's scout training with Bee lands them in the clutches of Starscream who tests an evil experiment on them.

added.title: Nexo Creativo
added.description: Cuando KO queda atrapado dentro de un lugar misterioso, se encuentra con otros héroes de Cartoon Network y todos se unen para escapar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Potencial Desperdiciado
added.description: A raíz de la victoria de la temporada anterior, los ninjas se han ablandado y el Maestro Wu debe recordarles quiénes son realmente.

added.title: Ventila-hala
added.description: Chef le confisca la mega-bola a Owen y la guarda en su oficina. Duncan, viendo una oportunidad para conseguir ayuda escapando de la guardaería, lidera un equipo de fuga por los conductos del aire acondicionado para recuperarla.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 1
added.description: Now on his own, Ben sets out to be a solo superhero, with new alien heroes at his disposal, but Grandpa Max has other plans. (Introducing Rook, Malware, Khyber, Nemetrix alien Crabdozer, new Ben aliens Feedback & Blox, Pakmar.)

added.title: Buscando Misiones
added.description: Al darse cuenta de que se han ablandado, el ninja busca una misión para reactivar su entrenamiento de Spinjitzu. Desafortunadamente, la ciudad de NINJAGO está disfrutando de un período de rara tranquilidad.

added.title: Jugo arcoiris
added.description: Después de desafiarse unos a otros a tomar el Latte de Pegaso de Chef, Izzy y Jude están llenos de energía y Duncan y Courtney hacen un viaje por carretera para tratar de reemplazar la bebida antes de que Chef descubra que desapareció.

added.title: Hard Times in Silicon City
added.description: Mega Man must stop Blasto Woman from plundering the Museum of the Hard Age and its cache of military grade weaponry.

added.title: Tripping the Light Fantastic
added.description: Mega Man tries to save Dr. Light from a date with "Mari," who's actually Hypno Woman in disguise!

added.title: Running Wild
added.description: Student elections get blown out of proportion (literally) when Air Man lends his support to Aki's rival for class president, Peter Punk.

added.title: #CortoCircuito
added.description: Leslie Willis, la chica mas cruel de la escuela, se convierte en una sensación de las redes sociales al subir videos malintencionados a su canal, haciendo que Wonder Woman cuestione la integridad moral de quienes viven en el Mundo del Hombre.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #ShockItToMe
added.description: Leslie Willis, the meanest girl in school, becomes a social media sensation by posting mean-spirited videos on her MetropoVids channel, causing Wonder Woman to question the moral integrity of the people who live in the World of Man.

added.title: Unfriendly Competition
added.description: Aki must set aside a petty rivalry with Bert Wily in order to stop Chemistry Man from wreaking havoc at Silicon Central's Field Day.

added.title: #AunqueSeaGigante
added.description: Karen Beecher siempre es molestada en la escuela. Pero cuando el centro comercial es atacado por una monstruosa super villana llamada Giganta, Karen descubre que la diminuta Bumblebee puede ser la única suficientemente pequeña para salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #SheMightBeGiant
added.description: Karen Beecher is always getting picked on at school, but when the local mall is attacked by a monstrous supervillain called Giganta, she discovers that tiny Bumblebee might be the only one small enough to save the day.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Fire Man and Wave Man team up to evaporate the city's water supply, forcing Mega Man to team up with an ally of his own- Suna.

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Subterranean Homesick Blues/Honey Struck
added.description: Subterranean Homesick Blues: The AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years more advanced./Honey Struck: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan who is nothing but sticky trouble.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Shun Shine/Ronin Son
added.description: Shun Shine: The AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell./Ronin Son: When Shun's cousin Masato Kazami claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend by their side.

added.title: Man Up 2: Still Man-ing
added.description: When someone steals all the water in Townsville, it's up to the girls to race through the Townsville Wastelands to get it back.

added.title: Framing Device/Bad Actors
added.description: Framing Device: When confronted by China Riot Lia learns to evolve Pegatrix after realizing the true meaning behind her filming obsession./Bad Actors: Dan tries to lie about evolving Drago and gets exposed while the team face off against Duran Dane and his unhappy Bakugan Nillious.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Los reyes de los Churros
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val comienzan a hacer dinero con la venta de churros en el puesto de tacos, su deseo por objetos los obliga a emplear trucos sucios para eliminar a la competencia.

added.title: Tiene Que Importarte
added.description: Cuando un viejo amigo de Enid llega a la ciudad, ella tiene la oportunidad de enmendar un error del pasado.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Cena en el Arroyo
added.description: Bernard queda a cargo de sus hermanos durante la noche, así que Craig se va a buscar su propia cena en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Buscando a Jessica
added.description: Jessica se adentra en un Arroyo desconocido, iy Craig debe encontrarla antes de que su madre se dé cuenta!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Hogar, dulce hogar
added.description: Los Fantásticos vuelven a casa y se dan cuenta de que el tiempo no ha pasado. Pronto descubren que su conocimiento acerca de las batallas ha aumentado de forma exponencial.

added.title: Ciudad de bichos
added.description: Craig descubre un montón de insectos bajo una roca y decide construirles una ciudad.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Un golpe de ternura
added.description: Después de derrotar a Strata, Los Fantásticos se dan cuenta de que no volvieron solos, sino con un Bakugan parecido a un panda que les dará muchos problemas.

added.title: El hijo prodigo
added.description: Mientras los Fantásticos intentan evolucionar a sus Bakugan como lo hizo Dan con Drago, el primo de Shun, Masato, llega a la ciudad para llevarlo de regreso a Japón.

added.title: El poder interior
added.description: Masato Kazami vuelve junto con los guardaespaldas de la familia para llevar a Shun a Japón, pero esta vez, Shun y Hydorous tienen una sorpresa preparada.

added.title: El baul de los recuerdos
added.description: Al ser confrontada por China Riot, Lia logra evolucionar a Pegatrix cuando comprende la verdadera razón de su obsesión por las cámaras.

added.title: Malos actores
added.description: Alguien expone a Dan por mentir acerca de la evolución de Drago, mientras el equipo se enfrenta a Duran Dane y su desdichado Bakugan, Nillious.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: The Secret of Dos Santos
added.description: Ben and Rook join Kai Green on a perilous alien relic hunt through South America.

added.title: The Most Dangerous Game Show
added.description: Ben fights for his life on an alien reality show.

added.title: La captura de Colosal
added.description: Colosal se cansa de sus responsabilidades en el cuartel general de sheriff y decide unirse a los Piratas del Cielo.

added.title: Fiebre de la baya de azúcar
added.description: Mao Mao intenta ocultar su amor por el pastel de fruta.

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

added.title: #SuperWho?
added.description: Overwhelmed by the amount of Superman coverage in Metropolis, Supergirl decides to get out there and really show the city what she can do. But when Superman inadvertently puts everyone in harm's way, Supergirl has to decide whether to do what's good for the people or what's good for her ego.

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Drilling Deep
added.description: At school, Aki struggles with the side effects of his newly replicated Drill Man schematics; later, as Mega Man, he learns to control his Fire Powers in thwarting Drill Man's assault on Skyraisers Inc.

added.title: Videodrone
added.description: Mega Man must stop Hypno Woman from turning the students and teachers at Silicon Central into her mindless drones.

added.title: Please Rush Home
added.description: A misunderstanding between Mega Man and Rush ends in the robo-pup running away from home, only to be reunited and reconciled during a confrontation with Wave Man.

added.title: Blaze of Glory
added.description: Mega Man and Suna must overcome a sibling dispute over what to do on their day off in order to stop Fire Man from overheating the city.

added.title: Nice on Ice
added.description: An "unscheduled" TV appearance not only lands Aki in hot water for missing class, but sets Ice Man on a misguided mission to "unite" (i.e. freeze together) every human and robot couple in the city!

added.title: The Mask of Deception
added.description: When an unknown criminal syndicate threatens the Royal Family, the Ninja are called back into action and must protect the royal princess and a fabled artifact that may hold supernatural powers.

added.title: The Jade Princess
added.description: In the wake of a vicious attack upon the palace, the Sons of Garmadon steal the second Oni Mask, and the ninja invite the royal princess, Harumi, into their makeshift family.

added.title: The Oni & the Dragon
added.description: While Princess Harumi adjusts to life with the ninja, Lloyd and Jay search for answers about the Oni Masks, while Cole and Zane attempt to infiltrate the Sons of Garmadon.

added.title: Snake Jaguar
added.description: In order to join the Sons of Garmadon, Zane (aka Snake Jaguar) participates in a deadly motorcycle initiation race.

added.title: Dead Man's Squall
added.description: Zane's near demise at the hands of Mr. E forces the ninja to flee aboard the Bounty, where they discover that a transmission Zane intercepted may reveal the hidden location of the Quiet One.

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 1
added.description: The Decepticons compete to be the first to bring Megatron Optimus Prime's spark while Hot Rod chases the "Moon Cheetah."

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 2
added.description: Slipstream searches for her missing Seekers while Hot Rod's "Moon Cheetah" chase brings him unexpectedly aboard the Nemesis.

added.title: Trials Part 1
added.description: Following the network of GroundBridges left by the Allspark, Optimus and Megatron finally discover the Allspark, and its Guardian, Cheetor.

added.title: Trials Part 2
added.description: Cheetor attempts to judge whether Optimus or Megatron are more worthy of the Allspark, but an unexpected visitor dashes all the bots' plans.

added.title: Dark Birth Part 1
added.description: While Starscream acquires new power through the Allspark, the Autobots mistakenly assume Starscream is still under Megatron's command.

added.title: Dark Birth Part 2
added.description: The Autobots and Decepticons battle aboard the Nemesis while Starscream uses the Allspark and Vector Sigma to create new allies.

added.title: Lego DC Batman: Family Matters
added.description: Ominous notes sent to the Bat-family have the nocturnal heroes racing against time to stop the villainous Red Hood, who's gathering Gotham City's rogues' gallery to enact revenge on the Dark Knight. As the origins of the Red Hood are slowly revealed, a threat emerges, one that will put Gotham under the watchful and dangerous glare of Brother Eye! Now it's up to Batman to face the past in order to save the future.

added.title: La mascara del engano
added.description: Cuando un sindicato de criminals desconocido amenaza a la Familia Real, los ninjas son llamados de nuevo a la acción y deben proteger a la princesa real y un artefacto legendario que puede tener poderes sobrenaturales.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: La princesa de jade
added.description: A raíz de un cruel ataque al Palacio, Los Hijos de Garmadon roban la segunda Máscara Oni, y los ninjas invitan a la Princesa Real, Harumi, a su improvisada familia.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El oni y el dragon
added.description: Mientras que la Princesa Harumi se adapta a la vida con los ninjas, Lloyd y Jay buscan respuestas sobre las máscaras Oni, mientras que Cole y Zane intentan infiltrarse en Los Hijos de Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Guar serpiente
added.description: Para unirse a Los Hijos de Garmadon, Zane (alias Jaguar Serpiente) participa en una carrera de iniciación mortal de motocicletas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El chillido de hombre muerto
added.description: La casi desaparición de Zane a manos del Señor "E" obliga a los ninjas a huir a bordo del Bounty, donde descubren que una tramisión que Zane interceptó puede revelar la ubicación oculta del "Silencioso".
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Bombazobo Vive
added.description: Durante un viaje de rutina al DMV, Max toma un examen de manejo para renovar su licencia. Pero cuando Zombozo, disfrazado, se apropia del papel del instructor, Ben se convierte en alienígena para detener al malvado y salvar el viaje familiar.

added.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
added.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

added.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
added.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Aventura en el laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Atrapados en la jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Jextra Perrestre
added.description: JP cree que puede ser de otro planeta, así que Craig trata de ayudarlo a hacer contacto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Demonios internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Una extrana conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: Mision para llevar
added.description: Kelsey guía a sus amigos en la misión más importante de la historia: buscar la comida para la cena.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Sigue tus suenos
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín necesitan encontrar un sueño que perseguir para que sus vidas tengan un rumbo.

added.title: Jefe de Cocina
added.description: Mao Mao se enfrenta a Colosal en una competencia para determinar si cocinar (y ser un héroe) es un arte o una ciencia.

added.title: El dia del hamster
added.description: Owen toma el trabajo de cuidar al hamster de la clase y descubre que es malvado.

added.title: Ego - egoista
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla tienen que demostrar que no son egoístas cuando hacen sus buenas acciones.

added.title: El comienzo de Cobrangutan
added.description: Mao Mao incita a Cobrangután y a los Piratas del Cielo a convertirse en villanos verdaderamente malvados, dignos de un héroe legendario como él.

added.title: Fuera de hora
added.description: Cuando las advertencias de Harold de no meterse con el reloj son ignoradas, los niños están obligados a salvarse a sí mismos cuando Duncan abre un agujero en la trama del tiempo.

added.title: Apoca-piojos ahora
added.description: Cuando Chef pacta una tregua con los piojos seleccionando tres niños que los "alberguen" en sus cabezas, Courtney instiga una guerra de niños contra piojos.

added.title: La super moto
added.description: Duncan hace que Beth crea que rompió su bicicleta impulsada a batería y hace que lo lleve de un lugar a otro en su carrito todo el día como castigo.

added.title: Venganza apestosa
added.description: Cuando una mofeta viene a buscar su venganza anual contra el Chef, Duncan ve una oportunidad de tomarse unas vacaciones de la guardería.

added.title: El Dia del Perro Caliente
added.description: Después de que olvida organizar el Día del Perro Caliente, Chef contrata a un actor disfrazado de canguro para representar al Señor Perro Salchicha Picante, creyendo que será un sustituto adecuado.

added.title: Gno mas buen senor
added.description: Cuando  la guardería es invadida por gnomos malvados, Duncan se encuentra en el equipo equivocado.

added.title: Harold Matamoscas y el caliz de moscas
added.description: Después de descubrir lo que cree que es una varita mágica, Owen convierte accidentalmente a Harold en una mosca común.

added.title: Enfrenta tus miedos

added.title: La formula de Manzana

added.title: Salchichas y dulce golpe

added.title: Manzallin
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín quieren llevarse el crédito de haber creado una nueva moda de baile.
